# Applications — folder structure

Every project under `applications/` uses this layout. Shared application rules live only in root `.cursor/rules/`. Do not keep parallel copies under `applications/rules/`, `applications/.cursor/`, or `applications/{project}/.cursor/`.

## Required layout per project

`applications/{project}/`

1. **Project root** — build scripts and project-level config only (e.g. `build_*_docs.py`).
2. **`documents/`** — exactly three synced deliverables:
   - `{project}_pdf.pdf`
   - `{project}_ppt.pptx`
   - `{project}_word.docx`
   No drafts, duplicates, or legacy copies in this folder or elsewhere in the project.
3. **`rules/`** — call-specific rules only (typically `source_of_truth.mdc`). One copy; never mirror the same file under `.cursor/`.

## Shared rules

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `.cursor/rules/folder_structure.mdc` | This layout |
| `.cursor/rules/documents.mdc` | Cross-format document sync |

## Assets & temp

- Media may come from repo `assets/` or a project `assets/` subfolder.
- Final edited docs live only in `documents/`.
- Temporary and build artifacts go in repo `tmp/` (gitignored).

## Example

```
.cursor/rules/
  folder_structure.mdc
  documents.mdc
applications/
  {project}/
    build_{project}_docs.py
    rules/
      source_of_truth.mdc
    documents/
      {project}_pdf.pdf
      {project}_ppt.pptx
      {project}_word.docx
```

Apply this to every `applications/` project. No duplicate deliverables and no duplicate rule trees for the same content.
